crutcher
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a worker who crutches [i.e. removes wool from belly and hindquarters of sheep prior to winter and lambing ,often itinerant, working in pairs or small gangs.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:crutch
Pronunciation:
